				<p>So other than selecting one of the other answers, I'm stuck with the bad one, correct?</p>
			</div>
			<div id = "comment-2680" class = "comment">
				<p>In this case I'm pretty sure that what's gong in is that people aren't completely testing the answer. I have the same behavior as the answer describes, but over time, the "solution" wears off. If it's "helping", it's actually misleading.</p>
